pale /peɪl/

(paling,paled,paler,pales,palest) 

1. ADJ If something is pale , it is very light in colour or almost white. 浅色的; 灰白的 

例： Migrating birds filled the pale sky. 迁徙的鸟布满了灰白的天空。 

例： As we age, our skin becomes paler. 随着我们变老，我们的皮肤变得更加苍白。 

2. COMB in COLOR Pale is also a combining form. (用于构成合成词) 浅…色的 

例： ...a pale blue sailor dress. …一件浅蓝色的水手服。 

3. ADJ If someone looks pale , their face looks a lighter colour than usual, usually because they are ill, frightened, or shocked. (脸色) 苍白的 

例： She looked pale and tired. 她看起来苍白而疲惫。 

4. V to make or become pale or paler; blanch 变白 

5. V-I If one thing pales in comparison with another, it is made to seem much less important, serious, or good by it. 显得逊色; 相形见绌 

例： When someone you love has a life-threatening illness, everything else pales in comparison. 当你所爱的人得了致命的疾病时，其他的一切就都显得不重要了。 

6. N a wooden post or strip used as an upright member in a fence (藩篱上的)木条; 木桩 

7. PHRASE outside the limits of social convention

